divs: Sighting DetailsLaying in bed around 1am tv on low volume, i herd a loud pulsating hum coming from out side at first i thought it was a car out side the house but when i looked out the window there was no cars out there the street lights were of due to the councils energy saving policy and go off around midnight. I could still hear the humming but could not see anything it was pitch black out side darker than normal (no moon light) our road is a deadend road and not close to any main roads that get a lot of traffic. The pulsating Hum was herd for about 15 mins and then just stopped. About 2 days later it happened again the same way, i have not herd it since
